The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 December is 123,963 (14,287.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 December, there were 5,486 new confirmed cases (632.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 December, there were 5,721 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (235 fewer cases).
